The British Airways
shopping portal

00:18:45.410 --> 00:18:47.340
at the moment-- they're
working really hard, actually,

00:18:47.340 --> 00:18:49.580
to try and reach the public,
because people really

00:18:49.580 --> 00:18:51.830
don't know about the
shopping portals.

00:18:51.830 --> 00:18:55.800
And they offer multiples of
Avios on all your purchasing.

00:18:55.800 --> 00:18:58.870
So Asos has an
offer at the moment.

00:18:58.870 --> 00:19:03.063
Eight Avios per pound when you
spend at Asos, which is a lot.

00:19:03.063 --> 00:19:04.730
Loads of people-- I
know loads of people

00:19:04.730 --> 00:19:07.070
spending 100 quid, 200
quid almost every week.

00:19:07.070 --> 00:19:09.550
So that's thousands and
thousands more Avios.

00:19:09.550 --> 00:19:13.440
And almost every online
retailer has that as an option.

00:19:13.440 --> 00:19:16.432
There's way more, but
even those three things

00:19:16.432 --> 00:19:17.390
will have you earning--

00:19:17.390 --> 00:19:18.740
BRIAN KELLY: Who here
shops online and earns

00:19:18.740 --> 00:19:20.450
airline miles for the purchases?

00:19:22.390 --> 00:19:23.890
NICKY KELVIN: So
that's pretty good.

00:19:23.890 --> 00:19:25.550
But of the rest of you who
didn't have your hand up,

00:19:25.550 --> 00:19:28.223
I imagine all of you are buying
stuff online almost every day.

00:19:28.223 --> 00:19:29.890
BRIAN KELLY: And by
clicking the portal,

00:19:29.890 --> 00:19:31.690
you literally are just
throwing miles in the trash.

00:19:31.690 --> 00:19:32.930
So always-- it's so simple.

00:19:32.930 --> 00:19:35.410
You just put your frequent
flyer number in on the portal.

00:19:35.410 --> 00:19:36.450
It puts a cookie
on your computer,

00:19:36.450 --> 00:19:37.908
and then you earn
miles in addition

00:19:37.908 --> 00:19:39.700
to the miles from
the credit card.

00:19:39.700 --> 00:19:40.550
NICKY KELVIN: Yeah.

00:19:40.550 --> 00:19:41.080
LESLIE TOBIN: OK.

00:19:41.080 --> 00:19:42.497
So what credit
cards would you say

00:19:42.497 --> 00:19:45.190
are the absolute top
three UK credit cards

00:19:45.190 --> 00:19:46.060
that you could get--

00:19:46.060 --> 00:19:47.120
NICKY KELVIN: OK,
so I'd say that--

00:19:47.120 --> 00:19:48.700
LESLIE TOBIN: --in
terms of point schemes?

00:19:48.700 --> 00:19:50.533
NICKY KELVIN: So that
Amex Preferred Rewards

00:19:50.533 --> 00:19:54.040
Gold is a great starter
card because no annual fee,

00:19:54.040 --> 00:19:55.630
eases you into everything.

00:19:55.630 --> 00:19:57.500
10,000 points is not
to be sniffed at.

00:19:57.500 --> 00:19:58.520
It's pretty good.

00:19:58.520 --> 00:20:00.627
And as I said before,
membership reward's

00:20:00.627 --> 00:20:02.710
really flexible, because
you can transfer them out

00:20:02.710 --> 00:20:04.620
to different places.

00:20:04.620 --> 00:20:07.420
That card also allows
you to double on travel

00:20:07.420 --> 00:20:08.830
and international spend.

00:20:08.830 --> 00:20:10.750
Actually, the fees on
the international spend

00:20:10.750 --> 00:20:12.640
may mean it doesn't
make sense to use it,

00:20:12.640 --> 00:20:14.710
but on travel, it's pretty good.

00:20:14.710 --> 00:20:18.740
The next main one is the
British Airways Premium Plus

00:20:18.740 --> 00:20:21.790
Amex, 195 pound fee,
but in return, you

00:20:21.790 --> 00:20:25.060
get a 25,000 Avios sign-up
bonus, 1 and 1/2 Avios

00:20:25.060 --> 00:20:27.640
per pound on spending, which is
a really good ongoing earning

00:20:27.640 --> 00:20:29.140
rate, and the companion voucher.

00:20:29.140 --> 00:20:30.880
Once you spent 10
grand in a year,

00:20:30.880 --> 00:20:34.120
you get this voucher to be able
to buy a whole second ticket.

00:20:34.120 --> 00:20:36.140
You buy one ticket,
you get one free.

00:20:36.140 --> 00:20:37.790
So if you've got a
big bank of Avios,

00:20:37.790 --> 00:20:39.890
you double the value
of that bank of Avios.

00:20:39.890 --> 00:20:40.850
That's really great.

00:20:40.850 --> 00:20:44.467
And then the third one I'd say
Virgin Money have two Virgin

00:20:44.467 --> 00:20:45.550
Atlantic credit cards now.

00:20:45.550 --> 00:20:47.140
They're quite new to the market.

00:20:47.140 --> 00:20:50.230
And the really nice thing about
those is they are a MasterCard.

00:20:50.230 --> 00:20:52.420
So you can use Amex
in most places,

00:20:52.420 --> 00:20:54.070
but another thing
people say to me

00:20:54.070 --> 00:20:56.592
all the time is like, I
can never use an Amex.

00:20:56.592 --> 00:20:57.550
Like, it's so annoying.

00:20:57.550 --> 00:20:59.750
But actually, you can
use it everywhere online.

00:20:59.750 --> 00:21:01.930
But for the times when
you really can't use it,

00:21:01.930 --> 00:21:03.310
having a MasterCard.

00:21:03.310 --> 00:21:05.560
And the paid version, the
premium version of the card,

00:21:05.560 --> 00:21:08.050
earns 1 and 1/2 Virgin
miles per pound.

00:21:08.050 --> 00:21:12.980
So that's also a pretty good
sign-up, a pretty good earning

00:21:12.980 --> 00:21:13.690
rate.

00:21:13.690 --> 00:21:16.560
You earn 15,000
points to sign up.

00:21:16.560 --> 00:21:19.250
And, if any of you are passing
through a Virgin lounge,

00:21:19.250 --> 00:21:22.120
this is my top secret tip,
they have these little cards

00:21:22.120 --> 00:21:24.060
in Virgin lounges at the moment.

00:21:24.060 --> 00:21:26.930
And if you sign up via the
link they give you on the card,

00:21:26.930 --> 00:21:29.838
you earn 30,000 points
instead of 15,000.

00:21:29.838 --> 00:21:31.630
So if you find yourself
in a Virgin lounge,

00:21:31.630 --> 00:21:32.520
make sure you ask.

00:21:32.520 --> 00:21:34.750
They normally have a
flying club representative.

00:21:34.750 --> 00:21:36.170
But that's kind of crazy.

00:21:36.170 --> 00:21:37.680
I couldn't believe that that
was a thing when I was there.

00:21:37.680 --> 00:21:38.020
LESLIE TOBIN: Yeah.

00:21:38.020 --> 00:21:38.760
That's a good tip.

00:21:38.760 --> 00:21:39.220
NICKY KELVIN: Yeah.

00:21:39.220 --> 00:21:40.220
LESLIE TOBIN: All right.

00:21:40.220 --> 00:21:42.670
So another great way to earn
points is through airlines.

00:21:42.670 --> 00:21:44.967
What are your favorite
European airlines?

00:21:44.967 --> 00:21:46.300
BRIAN KELLY: I mean, I'll start.

00:21:46.300 --> 00:21:48.820
I love Lufhansa.

00:21:48.820 --> 00:21:51.280
Lufthansa first class
is my favorite way

00:21:51.280 --> 00:21:54.420
to get across the pond,
and it's a great value.

00:21:54.420 --> 00:21:57.700
70,000 Amex points
to Aeroplan, and you

00:21:57.700 --> 00:22:00.190
can fly Lufthansa
first class, which

00:22:00.190 --> 00:22:03.160
is like amazing seats, caviar.

00:22:03.160 --> 00:22:05.362
Lufthansa is the
number one purchaser

00:22:05.362 --> 00:22:06.320
of caviar in the world.

00:22:06.320 --> 00:22:08.362
They serve it on every
single first class flight,

00:22:08.362 --> 00:22:11.341
and they give you like a
little tennis ball sized--

00:22:11.341 --> 00:22:14.230
oh, just thinking about it now.

00:22:14.230 --> 00:22:16.870
So I like Lufthansa long haul.

00:22:16.870 --> 00:22:20.360
I just saw the new
Virgin Atlantic A350-C,

00:22:20.360 --> 00:22:23.260
which is a huge improvement.

00:22:23.260 --> 00:22:26.097
Virgin NBA have had very
outdated products for years,

00:22:26.097 --> 00:22:28.180
so they're finally, over
the next couple of years,

00:22:28.180 --> 00:22:28.680
investing.

00:22:28.680 --> 00:22:31.842
But yeah, my vote's Lufthansa.

00:22:31.842 --> 00:22:34.300
NICKY KELVIN: I think this is
maybe a controversial answer,

00:22:34.300 --> 00:22:35.285
maybe obvious--

00:22:35.285 --> 00:22:36.160
BRIAN KELLY: Ryanair!

00:22:36.160 --> 00:22:37.645
[LAUGHTER]

00:22:37.645 --> 00:22:41.540
NICKY KELVIN: --is Jet2 because
I'm from Leeds and so is Jet2.

00:22:41.540 --> 00:22:42.040
No.

00:22:44.920 --> 00:22:50.260
It's hard to knock
British Airways in the UK.

00:22:50.260 --> 00:22:52.640
The network is huge.

00:22:52.640 --> 00:22:54.880
You can get pretty
much anywhere.

00:22:54.880 --> 00:22:57.480
In terms of the air miles
scheme, Avios scheme,

00:22:57.480 --> 00:23:00.820
it's the easiest program to
earn with and to spend with.

00:23:00.820 --> 00:23:03.040
And just the
service they provide

00:23:03.040 --> 00:23:08.530
in terms of where you can get
to is unrivaled out of the UK,

00:23:08.530 --> 00:23:12.010
especially in Europe, where you
can pretty much fly anywhere

00:23:12.010 --> 00:23:14.950
in slight more style
and comfort, especially

00:23:14.950 --> 00:23:17.100
if you manage to earn status.

00:23:17.100 --> 00:23:18.520
And the airports are nice.

00:23:18.520 --> 00:23:20.228
I would always rather
fly out of Heathrow

00:23:20.228 --> 00:23:22.303
than I would out of Luton.

00:23:22.303 --> 00:23:23.720
BRIAN KELLY: And
just to be clear,

00:23:23.720 --> 00:23:25.210
we're not sponsored
by any airline.

00:23:25.210 --> 00:23:26.470
We pay for all of
our own flights.

00:23:26.470 --> 00:23:27.095
We always have.

00:23:27.095 --> 00:23:28.270
So all of our reviews--

00:23:28.270 --> 00:23:30.220
we don't take freebies.

00:23:30.220 --> 00:23:32.800
I just felt like saying that.

00:23:32.800 --> 00:23:35.560
Because he sounded
like a fanboy.

00:23:35.560 --> 00:23:38.080
NICKY KELVIN: I get on
planes, and straightaway I'm

00:23:38.080 --> 00:23:39.790
like taking pictures
of everything.

00:23:39.790 --> 00:23:42.460
And the crew are often
like, what are you doing?

00:23:42.460 --> 00:23:45.635
I'm like, I just
love planes so much.

00:23:45.635 --> 00:23:48.010
And I think they got a lot
people like that, so kind of--

00:23:48.010 --> 00:23:49.060
BRIAN KELLY: They take
you into the cockpit,

00:23:49.060 --> 00:23:49.940
give you a little pin.

00:23:49.940 --> 00:23:50.732
NICKY KELVIN: Yeah.

00:23:50.732 --> 00:23:51.658
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:51.658 --> 00:23:53.950
LESLIE TOBIN: So you kind of
made a joke about Ryanair,

00:23:53.950 --> 00:23:57.010
but honestly, Ryanair,
EasyJet, a lot of these--

00:23:57.010 --> 00:24:01.050
BRIAN KELLY: By the way, I flew
Ryanair Stansted to Edinburgh

00:24:01.050 --> 00:24:02.050
like a couple weeks ago.

00:24:02.050 --> 00:24:03.880
We went to Gleneagles,
which was awesome.

00:24:03.880 --> 00:24:07.198
If you ever want a fun
Scottish getaway, I loved it.

00:24:07.198 --> 00:24:07.990
I didn't golf once.

00:24:07.990 --> 00:24:10.000
I played with their
shooting dogs.

00:24:10.000 --> 00:24:12.430
They have these 10
adorable Labradors.

00:24:12.430 --> 00:24:13.222
I'm a huge dog guy.

00:24:13.222 --> 00:24:15.763
And we're literally just in a
cuddle puddle out in the field,

00:24:15.763 --> 00:24:16.810
playing with these Labs.

00:24:16.810 --> 00:24:17.950
I went skeet shooting.

00:24:17.950 --> 00:24:20.680
Anyway, so I did a
video review of Ryanair,

00:24:20.680 --> 00:24:24.203
and I did a taste testing
of other cuisine in-flight.

00:24:24.203 --> 00:24:25.120
LESLIE TOBIN: Cuisine.

00:24:25.120 --> 00:24:26.020
[LAUGHS]

00:24:26.020 --> 00:24:27.020
BRIAN KELLY: Stay tuned.

00:24:27.020 --> 00:24:27.760
I loved it.

00:24:27.760 --> 00:24:30.320
I felt like a king because
I paid for the exit row.

00:24:30.320 --> 00:24:33.550
And most airlines
won't police boarding,

00:24:33.550 --> 00:24:35.300
because everyone's a
lead or this or that.

00:24:35.300 --> 00:24:39.680
Like, Ryanair is like, with
like crazy enforcement,

00:24:39.680 --> 00:24:42.710
and I was the one sucker
who paid for the exit row,

00:24:42.710 --> 00:24:45.445
but anyway.

00:24:45.445 --> 00:24:46.820
But back to the
point of Ryanair,

00:24:46.820 --> 00:24:48.620
if you can save
cold, hard cash, it

00:24:48.620 --> 00:24:51.230
doesn't make sense to
pay triple the price

00:24:51.230 --> 00:24:52.910
to fly BA on a short flight.

00:24:52.910 --> 00:24:53.450
Who cares?

00:24:53.450 --> 00:24:57.110
BA economy is essentially
the same thing.

00:24:57.110 --> 00:25:00.290
It would never make sense to pay
$200 more to earn 1,000 Avios.

00:25:00.290 --> 00:25:02.060
The whole points game
is it's currency.

00:25:02.060 --> 00:25:04.640
And you've got to figure out
when you can win and when you

00:25:04.640 --> 00:25:05.270
don't.

00:25:05.270 --> 00:25:07.040
And certainly,
flying short haul,

00:25:07.040 --> 00:25:10.310
saving your miles for the
really expensive ones,

00:25:10.310 --> 00:25:11.560
it's all an arbitrage game.

00:25:11.560 --> 00:25:13.423
Another advanced
tactic, especially

00:25:13.423 --> 00:25:16.640
if you fly to see family in the
US or Asia, is buying miles.

00:25:16.640 --> 00:25:20.450
So Alaska Airlines sells miles
for less than $0.02 apiece.

00:25:20.450 --> 00:25:24.440
I fly first class back and
forth from here in New York.

00:25:24.440 --> 00:25:28.270
But we buy Alaska miles, so
it's 70,000 for BA first.

00:25:28.270 --> 00:25:30.800
So I'm buying one
way for $1,400 US.

00:25:30.800 --> 00:25:33.320
I mean, granted their taxes and
fees bring it's like $1,800.

00:25:33.320 --> 00:25:37.010
But I'm buying BA first for
$3,600 round trip, pretty much

00:25:37.010 --> 00:25:41.180
any day of the year,
when it sells for 12,000

00:25:41.180 --> 00:25:43.550
or even buying
business class is 6,000

00:25:43.550 --> 00:25:46.810
and upgrading so
that's an option.

00:25:46.810 --> 00:25:49.820
I know a lot of premium
travelers in the UK

00:25:49.820 --> 00:25:53.150
will buy currencies like
LifeMiles, Alaska miles,

00:25:53.150 --> 00:25:54.920
and then use them
to book flights,

00:25:54.920 --> 00:25:57.320
because you can't earn
them as quickly, so just

00:25:57.320 --> 00:25:59.360
another thing to think about.

00:25:59.360 --> 00:26:00.145
LESLIE TOBIN: OK.

00:26:00.145 --> 00:26:00.770
What about you?

00:26:00.770 --> 00:26:03.630
Ryanair, EasyJet, what's your--

00:26:03.630 --> 00:26:07.045
NICKY KELVIN: So I actually
