It reclines pretty far.

00:27:04.528 --> 00:27:07.070
I mean, I flew it three weeks
ago from New York to Amsterdam,

00:27:07.070 --> 00:27:09.852
and it was like totally fine.

00:27:09.852 --> 00:27:11.060
If you don't have the miles--

00:27:11.060 --> 00:27:13.750
for what airlines charge
last minute walk-up,

00:27:13.750 --> 00:27:17.060
American Airlines will
charge $2,500 coach,

00:27:17.060 --> 00:27:19.420
because one way is
priced so weirdly.

00:27:19.420 --> 00:27:21.980
Norwegian sells-- I
bought that ticket.

00:27:21.980 --> 00:27:23.210
My flight had been canceled.

00:27:23.210 --> 00:27:27.258
I ran to JFK, and was $700 US
last minute for this premium--

00:27:27.258 --> 00:27:28.800
but it's better than
premium economy.

00:27:28.800 --> 00:27:30.860
I mean, it's a pretty
stretched out seat.

00:27:30.860 --> 00:27:35.740
So I highly recommend
Norwegian Air, not sponsored.

00:27:35.740 --> 00:27:37.027
Just pure advice.

