in over 50 countries,

00:48:18.840 --> 00:48:20.553
some countries
worse than others.

00:48:20.553 --> 00:48:21.720
If you've heard of reports--

00:48:21.720 --> 00:48:25.260
I remember 2 and 1/2 years
ago listening about Chechnya.

00:48:25.260 --> 00:48:26.900
LGBT people are
being rounded up.

00:48:26.900 --> 00:48:28.530
There are actually
concentration camps.

00:48:28.530 --> 00:48:29.610
And I remember reading
"The New York Times"

00:48:29.610 --> 00:48:30.990
article being like--

00:48:30.990 --> 00:48:32.100
like, you know, you deny.

00:48:32.100 --> 00:48:33.640
This can't be happening.

00:48:33.640 --> 00:48:34.530
It's true.

00:48:34.530 --> 00:48:36.720
Jamaica, trans people
are killed every week.

00:48:36.720 --> 00:48:38.010
It's horrible for them there.

00:48:38.010 --> 00:48:41.790
So through Rainbow Railroad, you
can donate your airline miles,

00:48:41.790 --> 00:48:45.460
and they actually fly people
out and get them asylum.

00:48:45.460 --> 00:48:47.880
So I've been working with
them for the last three years.

00:48:47.880 --> 00:48:49.505
We're actually about
to do a $1 million

00:48:49.505 --> 00:48:51.650
donation campaign
around Pride this year.

00:48:51.650 --> 00:48:54.150
If any of you are going to be
in New York, it's World Pride.

00:48:54.150 --> 00:48:57.420
It's going to be the biggest
pride ever on multiple levels.

00:48:57.420 --> 00:49:01.350
But 50,000 miles can
help save someone's life.

00:49:01.350 --> 00:49:03.375
And you may think, oh,
a lot of huge charities

00:49:03.375 --> 00:49:05.500
will take your miles, and
they just liquidate them.

00:49:05.500 --> 00:49:08.070
But what happens with
Rainbow Railroad,

00:49:08.070 --> 00:49:09.870
they're in a huge pool,
and we book people.

00:49:09.870 --> 00:49:11.910
So I had the ability,
going to Toronto where

00:49:11.910 --> 00:49:13.810
a lot of our refugees live--

00:49:13.810 --> 00:49:16.410
or asylees-- and I
was out to dinner

00:49:16.410 --> 00:49:20.040
with like 20 of
these Chechnyan guys,

00:49:20.040 --> 00:49:21.780
slashes across their
face, everything.

00:49:21.780 --> 00:49:25.263
And they told me the minute the
plane took off from Moscow--

00:49:25.263 --> 00:49:26.430
because we have safe houses.

00:49:26.430 --> 00:49:27.667
We get them places.

00:49:27.667 --> 00:49:30.000
And to know that my frequent
flyer miles-- they actually

00:49:30.000 --> 00:49:31.083
connected me with the guy.

00:49:31.083 --> 00:49:33.392
And you know, the minute
the plane took off,

00:49:33.392 --> 00:49:34.350
I just started bawling.

00:49:34.350 --> 00:49:37.080
And to think my frequent
flyer miles-- like,

00:49:37.080 --> 00:49:39.510
yes, I love going to Tahiti.

00:49:39.510 --> 00:49:42.488
Help save someone's
life, there's

00:49:42.488 --> 00:49:43.780
no better feeling in the world.

00:49:43.780 --> 00:49:47.520
So there's a ton of charities
you can donate your points to,

00:49:47.520 --> 00:49:49.470
finding one that you
really connect with

00:49:49.470 --> 00:49:51.430
and getting involved.

00:49:51.430 --> 00:49:54.343
So yeah, points can
save people's lives.

